# AI Education Tutor for Remote India

## 📌 Description
This project is an AI-powered education tutor designed for students in remote areas with limited internet connectivity. It uses a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture combined with a lightweight Large Language Model (LLM) to deliver accurate and context-aware answers.

## 🧠 Core Technologies
- RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
- Lightweight LLM (TinyLlama / Distil models)
- Vector Database (FAISS / Chroma)
- Edge / Embedded System (ESP32 / Raspberry Pi)

## ⚙️ System Architecture

### 🔹 RAG Pipeline
1. User asks a question
2. Query is converted into embeddings
3. Relevant documents are retrieved from local database
4. Retrieved data is passed to LLM
5. LLM generates final answer

### 🔹 LLM (Scaled Down)
- Uses small, efficient models instead of large cloud models
- Optimized for low memory and low power devices
- Can run locally without continuous internet

## 🚀 Features
- 📚 Context-aware answers using RAG
- ⚡ Fast response with local processing
- 🌐 Works in low or no internet
- 💾 Offline knowledge base support
- 🗣️ Multi-language support (future scope)

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Hugging Face Transformers
- FAISS / ChromaDB


## 📉 Model Optimization (Scaling Down)
- Quantization (reducing model size)
- Pruning (removing unnecessary weights)
- Using distilled models (smaller LLMs)
- Running inference locally instead of cloud

## ▶️ How to Run
1. Install dependencies (`pip install -r requirements.txt`)
2. Load educational dataset
3. Create embeddings and store in vector DB
4. Run the RAG pipeline
5. Ask questions via interface

## 🌍 Impact
This solution provides affordable and accessible AI-based education to students in rural and underserved regions, reducing dependency on internet connectivity.
